Fix empty back-office on first boot: embed uSync schemas, reference uSync metapackage

The LocalGov.Umbraco packages ship uSync schema files that never reach
the host site, so consumers boot into an empty Umbraco back-office with
none of the lg* document types installed.

Three linked issues:

1. Directory.Build.props packs uSync/**/* as contentFiles\any\any\uSync\.
   Modern SDK-style PackageReference projects ignore contentFiles, so
   those files are never copied into the consumer's content root.
   (contentFiles is a packages.config-era mechanism.)

2. The runtime fallback (USyncDeploymentComponent) reads *embedded*
   resources via assembly.GetManifestResourceNames(), but the csproj
   items are <Content>, not <EmbeddedResource>. The component runs and
   silently copies nothing.

3. LocalGov.Umbraco.Core references only uSync.Core (the serializer).
   None of the packages reference uSync / uSync.BackOffice, so even
   if the schema files reached disk there are no handlers to import them
   on boot.

This patch:

- Switches uSync/**/* from Content to EmbeddedResource so the deployment
  component can find them and materialise them to /uSync/v13 on the host.
- Replaces the uSync.Core PackageReference in Core with uSync (the
  metapackage) so uSync.BackOffice handlers are available transitively
  to all consumers.
- Drops the now-unused uSync.Core PackageVersion entry.

Consumers must still add the following to appsettings.json so uSync
imports the freshly-deployed schema on startup:

  "uSync": { "Settings": { "ImportAtStartup": "All" } }

Follow-up (separate PR): have USyncDeploymentComponent trigger
ISyncService.Import(folder) itself when it deploys new files, so
consumers don't need the appsettings snippet at all.
---
diff --git a/Directory.Build.props b/Directory.Build.props
--- a/Directory.Build.props
+++ b/Directory.Build.props
@@ -23,10 +23,13 @@
     <FileVersion>1.0.0.0</FileVersion>
   </PropertyGroup>
 
-  <!-- uSync config files: the RCL SDK already includes them implicitly as Content.
-       Use Update (not Include) to set packaging metadata on the already-included items. -->
+  <!-- uSync config files ship as EmbeddedResource so the runtime deployment component
+       (LocalGov.Umbraco.Core.Components.USyncDeploymentComponent) can materialise them
+       to the host site's /uSync/v13 folder on first boot. contentFiles does not work
+       with SDK-style PackageReference projects. -->
   <ItemGroup>
-    <Content Update="uSync\**\*" CopyToOutputDirectory="PreserveNewest" Pack="true" PackagePath="contentFiles\any\any\uSync\" />
+    <Content Remove="uSync\**\*" />
+    <EmbeddedResource Include="uSync\**\*" />
   </ItemGroup>
 
   <!-- Umbraco Marketplace manifest: set pack metadata on the already-implicitly-included JSON file -->
diff --git a/Directory.Packages.props b/Directory.Packages.props
--- a/Directory.Packages.props
+++ b/Directory.Packages.props
@@ -13,9 +13,8 @@
     <PackageVersion Include="Umbraco.Cms.Imaging.ImageSharp" Version="13.12.1" />
     <PackageVersion Include="Umbraco.Forms" Version="13.8.0" />
 
-    <!-- uSync -->
+    <!-- uSync: the full metapackage pulls in uSync.BackOffice, required for startup import of embedded schemas -->
     <PackageVersion Include="uSync" Version="13.3.2" />
-    <PackageVersion Include="uSync.Core" Version="13.3.2" />
 
     <!-- Background tasks -->
     <PackageVersion Include="Cultiv.Hangfire" Version="3.1.2" />
diff --git a/src/LocalGov.Umbraco.Core/LocalGov.Umbraco.Core.csproj b/src/LocalGov.Umbraco.Core/LocalGov.Umbraco.Core.csproj
--- a/src/LocalGov.Umbraco.Core/LocalGov.Umbraco.Core.csproj
+++ b/src/LocalGov.Umbraco.Core/LocalGov.Umbraco.Core.csproj
@@ -11,7 +11,7 @@
   <ItemGroup>
     <PackageReference Include="Umbraco.Cms.Web.Website" />
     <PackageReference Include="Umbraco.Cms.Web.BackOffice" />
-    <PackageReference Include="uSync.Core" />
+    <PackageReference Include="uSync" />
   </ItemGroup>
 
   <!-- Embed uSync config files as content so they're included in the NuGet package -->
